HEADWORD: Diadrom
<hw>Di"a*drom</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>dia`dromos</grk> a running through; <grk>dia`</grk> through +
<grk>dro`mos</grk>, used as inf. aor. of <grk>tre`chw</grk> to
run.]</ety> <def>A complete course or vibration; time of vibration, as
of a pendulum.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Locke.</au></rj></p>

